- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Transport/WebSocket/WebSocketFrameReader.cs
    Stream-oriented reader for RFC 6455 frames.

    Constructor:
        WebSocketFrameReader(Stream stream, bool requireMask,
            long maxMessagePayloadBytes = 1_048_576)
        - requireMask=true on the server side (frames from clients
          MUST be masked, RFC 6455 §5.1) — false on the client
          side (frames from server MUST NOT be masked).
        - maxMessagePayloadBytes guards both single-frame and
          fragmented-message accumulation against the 1 MB ceiling
          mandated by Req 3.10.

    Public methods:
        Task<WebSocketReadResult> ReadFrameAsync(CancellationToken)
            One physical frame: parses FIN, RSV (must be 0),
            opcode, MASK bit, payload length (7 / 7+16 / 7+64),
            optional masking key, then reads and unmasks the
            payload. Returns:
              Frame    — header + payload OK
              EndOfStream — stream returned 0 before header/payload
                            could be filled
              ProtocolError — RSV bits set, unknown opcode,
                              fragmented control frame, control
                              payload > 125 bytes, or 64-bit
                              length MSB set
              MaskRequired / MaskForbidden — direction mismatch
              MessageTooBig — single frame payload > limit (does
                              NOT consume payload bytes)

        Task<WebSocketReadResult> ReadMessageAsync(CancellationToken)
            Higher-level: assembles fragmented Text/Binary
            messages, delivers control frames as their own
            results, parses Close payload (status code + reason),
            and validates UTF-8 on assembled Text messages
            (Req 3.10 / RFC 6455 §5.6 → close 1007 surface).
            Multi-frame accumulation also enforces the size
            ceiling (close 1009 surface).

    Static helpers (used by tests and by the future
    WebSocketServer / HandshakeProcessor):
        ParseCloseFrame(byte[]) → (code?, reason?)
            length 0 → (null, null), length 1 → caller treats as
            protocol error (ReadMessageAsync surfaces this), >=2
            → big-endian status code + UTF-8 reason (strict).
        IsValidUtf8(byte[]) → bool
            UTF8Encoding(throwOnInvalidBytes: true).GetCharCount.

    Notes:
        - Pure C# on the existing Core asmdef (no Unity engine
          references), so it runs in EditMode tests against
          MemoryStream without any PlayerLoop pumping.
        - All reads use Stream.ReadAsync(byte[], int, int, ct);
          no Memory<byte> overload required, which keeps it
          portable across the Unity .NET Standard 2.1 surface.
        - The reader keeps minimal state across calls: one
          per-instance scratch buffer and the in-progress message
          opcode + accumulator buffer. Each ReadFrameAsync call
          is otherwise stateless.

