- Packages/com.vtuber-system-base.core-ipc-foundation/Runtime/Core/Transport/WebSocket/WebSocketFrameWriter.cs
    Stream-oriented writer for RFC 6455 frames.

    Constructor:
        WebSocketFrameWriter(Stream stream, bool maskOutgoing,
            Func<uint>? maskingKeyProvider = null)
        - maskOutgoing=true on the client side (must mask),
          false on the server side (must not mask).
        - maskingKeyProvider injection makes mask values
          deterministic in tests (FixedMaskKey = 0xDEADBEEF);
          the production default uses
          RandomNumberGenerator.Create() for cryptographic-
          quality 32-bit keys.

    Public methods:
        Task WriteFrameAsync(bool fin, WebSocketOpcode opcode,
            ReadOnlyMemory<byte> payload, CancellationToken)
            Generic primitive — writes one physical frame.
            Validates: known opcode (else ArgumentOutOfRangeException),
            fragmented control frame rejected (else
            ArgumentException), control payload > 125 bytes
            rejected (else ArgumentException). Acquires a per-
            instance SemaphoreSlim so concurrent WriteFrameAsync
            calls cannot interleave bytes on the wire. Flushes
            after each frame.
        Task WriteTextMessageAsync(string text, CancellationToken)
            UTF-8 encodes and writes a single FIN=1 Text frame.
        Task WritePingAsync(ReadOnlyMemory<byte>, CancellationToken)
        Task WritePongAsync(ReadOnlyMemory<byte>, CancellationToken)
        Task WriteCloseAsync(WebSocketCloseCode code,
            string? reason, CancellationToken)
            Builds the standard close payload (2-byte big-endian
            status code + UTF-8 reason). Rejects payloads > 125
            bytes (per control-frame rule).

    Static helper:
        EncodeFrame(bool fin, WebSocketOpcode opcode,
            ReadOnlySpan<byte> payload, uint? maskingKey) → byte[]
            Pure-function encoder used by WriteFrameAsync and by
            tests that want to craft a frame without a Stream.
            Picks 7-bit / 7+16-bit / 7+64-bit payload-length
            encoding by size, applies XOR masking when a key is
            present, sets FIN/MASK header bits accordingly.

    Notes:
        - Pure C# on the existing Core asmdef.
        - Disposing the writer disposes the SemaphoreSlim only;
          the underlying Stream lifetime is owned by the caller
          (WebSocketServer / WebSocketClient in tasks 4.3 / 4.4).

